            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">1.401</ph> Definition.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <p class="- topic/p ">“Deviation” means any one or combination of the following:</p>
			      <ol id="d37e16" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d39e20" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The issuance or use of a policy, procedure, solicitation provision (see definition in <xref href="FAR-i1125359.dita#i1125359"
                        base="i1125359"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>), contract clause (see definition in <xref href="FAR-i1125359.dita#i1125359"
                        base="i1125359"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>), method, or practice of conducting acquisition actions of any kind at any stage of the acquisition process that is inconsistent with the FAR.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d39e35" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The omission of any solicitation provision or contract clause when its prescription requires its use.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d39e44" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The use of any solicitation provision or contract clause with modified or alternate language that is not authorized by the FAR (see definition of “modification” in <xref href="FAR-i1064507.dita#i1064507"
                        base="i1064507"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.101</xref>(a) and definition of “alternate” in <xref href="FAR-i1125359.dita#i1125359"
                        base="i1125359"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>(a)).</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d39e59" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The use of a solicitation provision or contract clause prescribed by the FAR on a “substantially as follows” or “substantially the same as” basis (see definitions in <xref href="FAR-i1125359.dita#i1125359"
                        base="i1125359"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1064507.dita#i1064507"
                        base="i1064507"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.101</xref>(a)), if such use is inconsistent with the intent, principle, or substance of the prescription or related coverage on the subject matter in the FAR.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d39e74" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The authorization of lesser or greater limitations on the use of any solicitation provision, contract clause, policy, or procedure prescribed by the FAR.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d39e84" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(f)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The issuance of policies or procedures that govern the contracting process or otherwise control contracting relationships that are not incorporated into agency acquisition regulations in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1126703.dita#i1126703"
                        base="i1126703"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">1.301</xref>(a).</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
		    </conbody>
